cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an adversarial approach, which involves training a neural network to generate new samples, and this is a common technique in deep learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely. The paper also involves transfer learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates its approach on popular tracking benchmarks, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
